&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Antenna is the leading provider of data and analytics for subscription media services in the U.S. Antenna&#39;s standardized metrics, competitive benchmarks, syndicated insights, and market intelligence are trusted by some of the most recognized and respected brands across media and entertainment sectors. Using a proprietary AI-powered approach, Antenna connects subscription activities with real consumer viewership to provide services, studios, and creators with an unmatched, market-wide view of subscriber behaviors to better understand acquisition, retention, and engagement.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Interested in joining our team?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;Send us your resume and tell us why you&#39;d make a great addition!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Antenna&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Antenna is the leading provider of data and analytics for the U.S. Subscription Economy. Our standardized metrics, competitive benchmarks, syndicated insights, and market intelligence are used by some of the most trusted brands across media and entertainment sectors to better understand subscriber behavior and successfully navigate the rapidly changing consumer subscription landscape.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Founded in 2019 by Jonathan Carson, a successful serial entrepreneur with deep roots in data and analytics, and Rameez Tase, a seasoned executive in media and analytics, Antenna’s mission is supported by top investors with global expertise in media and technology: Raine Ventures, BDMI, UTA Ventures, and many more. Antenna is powered by a dedicated group of individuals who are intellectually curious, passionate about service, and committed to supporting the needs of Antenna clients and each other every day. As a small remote-first team, Antenna team members have the opportunity to work alongside senior leaders and professionally grow with an early-stage team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;https://www.antenna.live/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Antenna is the leading provider of data and analytics for subscription media services in the U.S. Antenna&#39;s standardized metrics, competitive benchmarks, syndicated insights, and market intelligence are trusted by some of the most recognized and respected brands across media and entertainment sectors. Using a proprietary AI-powered approach, Antenna connects subscription activities with real consumer viewership to provide services, studios, and creators with an unmatched, market-wide view of subscriber behaviors to better understand acquisition, retention, and engagement.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Senior Insight Analyst&lt;/strong&gt; to elevate the understanding of Antenna data by delivering best-in-class insights. At Antenna, the Insight Analyst team uses strategic, data-driven insights to fuel high-stakes business decisions. As a Senior Insight Analyst, you will partner with Client Services, Sales, and Marketing to transform complex data into relevant, actionable narratives. You will&amp;nbsp; manage complex, fast moving projects independently, mentor junior team members, and maintain a strategic focus on market trends.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will report to the Manager, Insight Analytics. Antenna is a remote-first company, and we are looking for candidates who can work during US business hours. Preferably, you should be based in a US time zone (Eastern, Central, Mountain, or Pacific).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extract and analyze Antenna data to tell compelling stories about the subscription economy; introduce novel analyses by leveraging creative, strategic data analysis methods&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Present findings external clients and internal stakeholders; translate complex datasets into clear, persuasive data stories&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support Client Service objectives by owning the production of Antenna’s monthly syndicated reports and crafting custom analyses in response to customer questions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support Sales and Marketing via key tentpole analyst reports, such as the quarterly State of Subscriptions, and support rapid response requests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use SQL to navigate Antenna’s databases; collaborate with Data Services to scope and extract custom cohorts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Orchestrate multiple project timelines and manage expectations across cross-functional stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a thought leader by monitoring subscription trends, emerging platforms, and relevant market events&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years of experience in data analytics with a proven track record of driving business strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience presenting data-driven insights to external clients or internal stakeholders, and executive leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expert proficiency in Excel and PowerPoint; some proficiency in SQL&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong storyteller who synthesizes complex data into intuitive narratives for diverse audiences, both verbally and in writing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Possesses uncompromising attention to detail and organizes massive datasets with precision&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-starter who prioritizes time effectively, meets tight deadlines, and thrives in a fast-paced startup environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bonus: Experience with Looker or similar Business Intelligence tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bonus: Deep interest in the Subscription Economy, including streaming services and key players in the digital subscription market&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
