&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Antenna is the leading provider of data and analytics for subscription media services in the U.S. Antenna&#39;s standardized metrics, competitive benchmarks, syndicated insights, and market intelligence are trusted by some of the most recognized and respected brands across media and entertainment sectors. Using a proprietary AI-powered approach, Antenna connects subscription activities with real consumer viewership to provide services, studios, and creators with an unmatched, market-wide view of subscriber behaviors to better understand acquisition, retention, and engagement.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Strategic Account Director &lt;/strong&gt;to drive expansion revenue, deepen our footprint within our largest media and entertainment accounts, and own how we grow strategic enterprise relationships. You will partner directly with executive leadership to set account strategy, build expansion roadmaps, mobilize cross-functional resources, and close the renewals and expansions that fuel Antenna&#39;s next phase of growth. You will deepen Antenna&#39;s engagement with VP and C-suite executives at the world&#39;s largest tech and media companies, translating complex data into clear business value. You will shift from landing initial expansion to growing each enterprise account.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will report to our VP, Client Services. Antenna is a remote-first company, and we are looking for candidates who can work during US business hours. Preferably, you should be based in a US time zone (Eastern, Central, Mountain, or Pacific).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own Enterprise Relationships &amp;amp; Revenue:&lt;/strong&gt; Own executive relationships (VP+) at enterprise accounts to significantly grow revenue, hit renewal/expansion targets, and ensure clients realize ROI to become trusted advocates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive Strategic Account Planning:&lt;/strong&gt; Build and own long-term strategic account plans, mapping out multi-quarter expansion roadmaps that balance short-term wins with a long-term product vision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partner with Customer Success and Insights:&lt;/strong&gt; Collaborate closely with Customer Success Managers (CSMs) as your account partners and Insights &amp;amp; Analytics team as your insight partners; leverage their day-to-day insights, data expertise, and user relationships to identify upsell opportunities and strategic executive intros, while hunting for new internal relationships to pass back to the CSM team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead Renewal &amp;amp; Deal Execution:&lt;/strong&gt; Own the end-to-end renewal strategy with a 90-day runway, while managing client expectations and ensuring internal alignment throughout the entire deal cycle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Uncover &amp;amp; Execute New Opportunities:&lt;/strong&gt; Conduct client discovery for advanced solutions and new products in development, running use-case and value-proposition deep dives to expand Antenna’s footprint.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Enterprise &amp;amp; Executive Sales Expert:&lt;/strong&gt; You have a proven track record of executing high-velocity, consultative new business sales, building multi-threaded relationships with VP and C-suite executives, and delivering white-glove service.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data &amp;amp; Product Literate:&lt;/strong&gt; You are comfortable selling complex, multi-SKU data products and working with Product/Engineering teams. You speak the language of programming, audience measurement, and subscriber growth, translating data into the strategic questions Media &amp;amp; Entertainment leaders care about (launches, pricing, bundling, content slates).&lt;/li
